    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted 2008 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L V8. This naturally aspirated unit features individual throttle bodies and an 8,400 RPM redline, mated to a precise 6-speed manual gearbox. Key preventative maintenance has been addressed, including rod bearing replacement with VAC treated shells and updated throttle actuators. The chassis is equipped with Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and the Variable M Differential Lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution and lateral stability. The hydraulic steering rack offers excellent feedback, a hallmark of this generation. While the aesthetic condition shows light evidence of spirited use, the drivetrain remains tight with no subframe fatigue or VANOS issues. A compelling, driver-spec example for the discerning enthusiast.",
